To support a desktop installation, the application developer can use the Application Manager to automatically download the appropriate .cab file to the end user\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s device. The appl\hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
ication developer can write a single desktop setup program that registers the application with AppManager by specifying all the .cab files in the CeAppMgr .ini file. Here is an example of the CeAppMgr .ini file MyApp.ini:
\par }\pard\plain \s39\ql \li0\ri0\sl-220\slmult0\widctlpar\tx390\tx780\tx1170\tx1560\tx1950\tx2340\tx2730\tx3120\tx3510\tx3900\tx4290\tx4680\tx5070\tx5460\tx5850\tx6240\tx6630\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
\f106\fs16\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\insrsid12476003 
\par [CEAppManager]
\par Version        = 1.0\tab ; this is the CeAppMgr .ini version, not the app version}{\i\insrsid12476003 
\par }{\insrsid12476003 Component  = MyApplication}{\i\insrsid12476003 
\par }{\insrsid12476003 
\par [MyApplication]
\par Description   = Sample Windows CE application
\par CabFiles       = MyApp.HPC_SH3.cab,MyApp.PPC_SH3.cab,MyApp.HPCPRO_ARM.cab
\par \tab ; note that there are no extra spaces between the list of .cab files
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\tx450\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe2052\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af13\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp2052 {\insrsid12476003 \hich\af0\dbch\af13\loch\f0 
Invoking CeAppMgr with the .ini file registers the application and its associated .cab files, so that the end user can download the application on the next connection.
\par }\pard\plain \s39\ql \li0\ri0\sl-220\slmult0\widctlpar\tx390\tx780\tx1170\tx1560\tx1950\tx2340\tx2730\tx3120\tx3510\tx3900\tx4290\tx4680\tx5070\tx5460\tx5850\tx6240\tx6630\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 
